{
  "video_id": "pWaxi4H2xPU",
  "title": "What We Don’t Talk About When We Talk About Love | Mandy Len Catron | TEDxSFU",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 7508.0,
      "end_time": 8658.0,
      "text": "Hi, you guys!"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 9429.0,
      "end_time": 11825.0,
      "text": "Thank you for sticking around till the end."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 11849.0,
      "end_time": 12849.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 12873.0,
      "end_time": 15508.0,
      "text": "I told my mom that no one would be here at the end,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 15532.0,
      "end_time": 18309.0,
      "text": "and she promised me that you guys would, so ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 18333.0,
      "end_time": 19665.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 20223.0,
      "end_time": 24523.0,
      "text": "OK, so today I want to talk about how we talk about love."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 24907.0,
      "end_time": 26570.0,
      "text": "And specifically,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 26810.0,
      "end_time": 29516.0,
      "text": "I want to talk about what's wrong with how we talk about love."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 30343.0,
      "end_time": 33750.0,
      "text": "Most of us will probably fall in love a few times"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 33774.0,
      "end_time": 35239.0,
      "text": "over the course of our lives,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 35263.0,
      "end_time": 39473.0,
      "text": "and in the English language, this metaphor, falling,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 39497.0,
      "end_time": 42511.0,
      "text": "is really the main way that we talk about that experience."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 43262.0,
      "end_time": 44413.0,
      "text": "I don't know about you,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 44437.0,
      "end_time": 46364.0,
      "text": "but when I conceptualize this metaphor,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 46388.0,
      "end_time": 49266.0,
      "text": "what I picture is straight out of a cartoon --"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 49746.0,
      "end_time": 51420.0,
      "text": "like there's a man,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 51660.0,
      "end_time": 52783.0,
      "text": "he's walking down the sidewalk,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 52807.0,
      "end_time": 55919.0,
      "text": "without realizing it, he crosses over an open manhole,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 55943.0,
      "end_time": 59604.0,
      "text": "and he just plummets into the sewer below."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 59628.0,
      "end_time": 63708.0,
      "text": "And I picture it this way because falling is not jumping."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 64438.0,
      "end_time": 66470.0,
      "text": "Falling is accidental,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 66495.0,
      "end_time": 68397.0,
      "text": "it's uncontrollable."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 68421.0,
      "end_time": 71946.0,
      "text": "It's something that happens to us without our consent."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 71970.0,
      "end_time": 76754.0,
      "text": "And this is the main way we talk about starting a new relationship."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 78600.0,
      "end_time": 81773.0,
      "text": "I am a writer and I'm also an English teacher,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 81797.0,
      "end_time": 84820.0,
      "text": "which means I think about words for a living."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 84106.0,
      "end_time": 88256.0,
      "text": "You could say that I get paid to argue that the language we use matters,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 88280.0,
      "end_time": 92480.0,
      "text": "and I would like to argue that many of the metaphors we use"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 92504.0,
      "end_time": 94710.0,
      "text": "to talk about love --"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 94950.0,
      "end_time": 95917.0,
      "text": "maybe even most of them --"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 95942.0,
      "end_time": 97342.0,
      "text": "are a problem."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 98370.0,
      "end_time": 100263.0,
      "text": "So, in love, we fall."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 101436.0,
      "end_time": 102901.0,
      "text": "We're struck."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 102925.0,
      "end_time": 104321.0,
      "text": "We are crushed."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 105100.0,
      "end_time": 106371.0,
      "text": "We swoon."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 106856.0,
      "end_time": 108652.0,
      "text": "We burn with passion."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 109408.0,
      "end_time": 111385.0,
      "text": "Love makes us crazy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 111409.0,
      "end_time": 112973.0,
      "text": "and it makes us sick."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 113466.0,
      "end_time": 114826.0,
      "text": "Our hearts ache,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 114850.0,
      "end_time": 116856.0,
      "text": "and then they break."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 117896.0,
      "end_time": 121400.0,
      "text": "So our metaphors equate the experience of loving someone"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 121640.0,
      "end_time": 123717.0,
      "text": "to extreme violence or illness."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 123741.0,
      "end_time": 125826.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 126771.0,
      "end_time": 127922.0,
      "text": "They do."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 127946.0,
      "end_time": 129929.0,
      "text": "And they position us as the victims"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 129953.0,
      "end_time": 133312.0,
      "text": "of unforeseen and totally unavoidable circumstances."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 134217.0,
      "end_time": 136940.0,
      "text": "My favorite one of these is \"smitten,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 136964.0,
      "end_time": 139818.0,
      "text": "which is the past participle of the word \"smite.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 139842.0,
      "end_time": 142910.0,
      "text": "And if you look this word up in the dictionary --"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 142934.0,
      "end_time": 143958.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 143982.0,
      "end_time": 148500.0,
      "text": "you will see that it can be defined as both \"grievous affliction,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 148524.0,
      "end_time": 151375.0,
      "text": "and, \"to be very much in love.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 153386.0,
      "end_time": 156730.0,
      "text": "I tend to associate the word \"smite\" with a very particular context,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 156754.0,
      "end_time": 158317.0,
      "text": "which is the Old Testament."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 159230.0,
      "end_time": 163977.0,
      "text": "In the Book of Exodus alone, there are 16 references to smiting,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 164200.0,
      "end_time": 167775.0,
      "text": "which is the word that the Bible uses for the vengeance of an angry God."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 167799.0,
      "end_time": 169520.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 169544.0,
      "end_time": 172249.0,
      "text": "Here we are using the same word to talk about love"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 172273.0,
      "end_time": 174698.0,
      "text": "that we use to explain a plague of locusts."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 174723.0,
      "end_time": 175751.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 175775.0,
      "end_time": 177310.0,
      "text": "Right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 177550.0,
      "end_time": 179147.0,
      "text": "So, how did this happen?"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 179171.0,
      "end_time": 183162.0,
      "text": "How have we come to associate love with great pain and suffering?"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 183186.0,
      "end_time": 187175.0,
      "text": "And why do we talk about this ostensibly good experience"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 187199.0,
      "end_time": 189303.0,
      "text": "as if we are victims?"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 190226.0,
      "end_time": 191917.0,
      "text": "These are difficult questions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 191941.0,
      "end_time": 193587.0,
      "text": "but I have some theories."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 193611.0,
      "end_time": 194850.0,
      "text": "And to think this through,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 194874.0,
      "end_time": 197502.0,
      "text": "I want to focus on one metaphor in particular,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 197526.0,
      "end_time": 199697.0,
      "text": "which is the idea of love as madness."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 200758.0,
      "end_time": 203465.0,
      "text": "When I first started researching romantic love,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 203489.0,
      "end_time": 206250.0,
      "text": "I found these madness metaphors everywhere."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 206274.0,
      "end_time": 208377.0,
      "text": "The history of Western culture"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 208401.0,
      "end_time": 212338.0,
      "text": "is full of language that equates love to mental illness."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 213110.0,
      "end_time": 215370.0,
      "text": "These are just a few examples."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 215610.0,
      "end_time": 216404.0,
      "text": "William Shakespeare:"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 216428.0,
      "end_time": 217861.0,
      "text": "\"Love is merely a madness,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 217885.0,
      "end_time": 219202.0,
      "text": "from \"As You Like It.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 219762.0,
      "end_time": 221190.0,
      "text": "Friedrich Nietzsche:"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 221430.0,
      "end_time": 223546.0,
      "text": "\"There is always some madness in love.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 224229.0,
      "end_time": 227950.0,
      "text": "\"Got me looking, got me looking so crazy in love --\""
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 227119.0,
      "end_time": 229188.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 229212.0,
      "end_time": 231810.0,
      "text": "from the great philosopher, Beyoncé Knowles."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 231834.0,
      "end_time": 233295.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 234753.0,
      "end_time": 237587.0,
      "text": "I fell in love for the first time when I was 20,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 237611.0,
      "end_time": 240790.0,
      "text": "and it was a pretty turbulent relationship right from the start."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 241129.0,
      "end_time": 244334.0,
      "text": "And it was long distance for the first couple of years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 244358.0,
      "end_time": 248954.0,
      "text": "so for me that meant very high highs and very low lows."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 249464.0,
      "end_time": 251668.0,
      "text": "I can remember one moment in particular."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 252250.0,
      "end_time": 255595.0,
      "text": "I was sitting on a bed in a hostel in South America,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 255619.0,
      "end_time": 259315.0,
      "text": "and I was watching the person I love walk out the door."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 259821.00000000003,
      "end_time": 261434.00000000003,
      "text": "And it was late,"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 261458.00000000003,
      "end_time": 262718.0,
      "text": "it was nearly midnight,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 262742.0,
      "end_time": 264719.0,
      "text": "we'd gotten into an argument over dinner,"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 264743.0,
      "end_time": 266692.0,
      "text": "and when we got back to our room,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 266716.0,
      "end_time": 269441.0,
      "text": "he threw his things in the bag and stormed out."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 270811.0,
      "end_time": 274700.0,
      "text": "While I can no longer remember what that argument was about,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 274940.0,
      "end_time": 278149.0,
      "text": "I very clearly remember how I felt watching him leave."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 278792.0,
      "end_time": 282337.0,
      "text": "I was 22, it was my first time in the developing world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 283940.0,
      "end_time": 285349.0,
      "text": "and I was totally alone."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 286820.0,
      "end_time": 289449.0,
      "text": "I had another week until my flight home,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 289473.0,
      "end_time": 291841.0,
      "text": "and I knew the name of the town that I was in,"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 291865.0,
      "end_time": 295448.0,
      "text": "and the name of the city that I needed to get to to fly out,"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 295472.0,
      "end_time": 298727.0,
      "text": "but I had no idea how to get around."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 299512.0,
      "end_time": 302689.0,
      "text": "I had no guidebook and very little money,"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 302713.0,
      "end_time": 304483.0,
      "text": "and I spoke no Spanish."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 305217.0,
      "end_time": 307313.0,
      "text": "Someone more adventurous than me"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 307338.0,
      "end_time": 309768.0,
      "text": "might have seen this as a moment of opportunity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 309792.0,
      "end_time": 311621.0,
      "text": "but I just froze."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 312760.0,
      "end_time": 313893.0,
      "text": "I just sat there."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 314408.0,
      "end_time": 316451.0,
      "text": "And then I burst into tears."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 317270.0,
      "end_time": 319397.0,
      "text": "But despite my panic,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 319422.0,
      "end_time": 321992.0,
      "text": "some small voice in my head thought,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 322160.0,
      "end_time": 324353.0,
      "text": "\"Wow. That was dramatic."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 324377.0,
      "end_time": 327760.0,
      "text": "I must really be doing this love thing right.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 327100.0,
      "end_time": 328888.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 328912.0,
      "end_time": 333431.0,
      "text": "Because some part of me wanted to feel miserable in love."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 333896.0,
      "end_time": 337336.0,
      "text": "And it sounds so strange to me now, but at 22,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 337360.0,
      "end_time": 340505.0,
      "text": "I longed to have dramatic experiences,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 340529.0,
      "end_time": 345727.0,
      "text": "and in that moment, I was irrational and furious and devastated,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 345751.0,
      "end_time": 346974.0,
      "text": "and weirdly enough,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 346999.0,
      "end_time": 350375.0,
      "text": "I thought that this somehow legitimized the feelings I had"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 350399.0,
      "end_time": 352238.0,
      "text": "for the guy who had just left me."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 353833.0,
      "end_time": 358196.0,
      "text": "I think on some level I wanted to feel a little bit crazy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 358220.0,
      "end_time": 361752.0,
      "text": "because I thought that that was how loved worked."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 362811.0,
      "end_time": 364618.0,
      "text": "This really should not be surprising,"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 364642.0,
      "end_time": 367960.0,
      "text": "considering that according to Wikipedia,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 367120.0,
      "end_time": 369393.0,
      "text": "there are eight films,"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 369417.0,
      "end_time": 371414.0,
      "text": "14 songs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 371438.0,
      "end_time": 374635.0,
      "text": "two albums and one novel with the title \"Crazy Love.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 375507.0,
      "end_time": 378633.0,
      "text": "About half an hour later, he came back to our room."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 378657.0,
      "end_time": 379808.0,
      "text": "We made up."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 379832.0,
      "end_time": 382649.0,
      "text": "We spent another mostly happy week traveling together."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 382673.0,
      "end_time": 384105.0,
      "text": "And then, when I got home,"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 384129.0,
      "end_time": 389113.0,
      "text": "I thought, \"That was so terrible and so great."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 389659.0,
      "end_time": 391373.0,
      "text": "This must be a real romance.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 392676.0,
      "end_time": 395376.0,
      "text": "I expected my first love to feel like madness,"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 395400.0,
      "end_time": 399179.0,
      "text": "and of course, it met that expectation very well."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 399611.0,
      "end_time": 401301.0,
      "text": "But loving someone like that --"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 401326.0,
      "end_time": 405421.0,
      "text": "as if my entire well-being depended on him loving me back --"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 405445.0,
      "end_time": 407538.0,
      "text": "was not very good for me"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 407562.0,
      "end_time": 408712.0,
      "text": "or for him."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 409520.0,
      "end_time": 413221.0,
      "text": "But I suspect this experience of love is not that unusual."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 413696.0,
      "end_time": 417907.0,
      "text": "Most of us do feel a bit mad in the early stages of romantic love."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 418485.0,
      "end_time": 422301.0,
      "text": "In fact, there is research to confirm that this is somewhat normal,"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 422950.0,
      "end_time": 424836.0,
      "text": "because, neurochemically speaking,"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 424860.0,
      "end_time": 429422.0,
      "text": "romantic love and mental illness are not that easily distinguished."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 430716.0,
      "end_time": 431867.0,
      "text": "This is true."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 431891.0,
      "end_time": 436450.0,
      "text": "This study from 1999 used blood tests"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 436474.0,
      "end_time": 439568.0,
      "text": "to confirm that the serotonin levels of the newly in love"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 439592.0,
      "end_time": 442389.0,
      "text": "very closely resembled the serotonin levels"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 442413.0,
      "end_time": 445718.0,
      "text": "of people who had been diagnosed with obsessive-compulsive disorder."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 445742.0,
      "end_time": 446750.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 446774.0,
      "end_time": 449471.0,
      "text": "Yes, and low levels of serotonin"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 449495.0,
      "end_time": 453970.0,
      "text": "are also associated with seasonal affective disorder"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 453121.0,
      "end_time": 454400.0,
      "text": "and depression."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 455357.0,
      "end_time": 457617.0,
      "text": "So there is some evidence"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 457641.0,
      "end_time": 461989.0,
      "text": "that love is associated with changes to our moods and our behaviors."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 462130.0,
      "end_time": 466200.0,
      "text": "And there are other studies to confirm"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 466440.0,
      "end_time": 469734.0,
      "text": "that most relationships begin this way."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 470330.0,
      "end_time": 474493.0,
      "text": "Researchers believe that the low levels of serotonin"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 474517.0,
      "end_time": 478552.0,
      "text": "is correlated with obsessive thinking about the object of love,"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 478576.0,
      "end_time": 482634.0,
      "text": "which is like this feeling that someone has set up camp in your brain."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 482658.0,
      "end_time": 485589.0,
      "text": "And most of us feel this way when we first fall in love."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 485613.0,
      "end_time": 488739.0,
      "text": "But the good news is, it doesn't always last that long --"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 488763.0,
      "end_time": 491936.0,
      "text": "usually from a few months to a couple of years."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 493220.0,
      "end_time": 495830.0,
      "text": "When I got back from my trip to South America,"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 495854.0,
      "end_time": 499431.0,
      "text": "I spent a lot of time alone in my room,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 499455.0,
      "end_time": 500794.0,
      "text": "checking my email,"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 500819.0,
      "end_time": 503182.0,
      "text": "desperate to hear from the guy I loved."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 504215.0,
      "end_time": 509563.0,
      "text": "I decided that if my friends could not understand my grievous affliction,"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 509587.0,
      "end_time": 511536.0,
      "text": "then I did not need their friendship."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 511560.0,
      "end_time": 513643.0,
      "text": "So I stopped hanging out with most of them."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 514570.00000000006,
      "end_time": 518251.00000000006,
      "text": "And it was probably the most unhappy year of my life."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 518756.0,
      "end_time": 522870.0,
      "text": "But I think I felt like it was my job to be miserable,"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 523519.0,
      "end_time": 525311.0,
      "text": "because if I could be miserable,"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 525335.0,
      "end_time": 528200.0,
      "text": "then I would prove how much I loved him."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 528260.0,
      "end_time": 529911.0,
      "text": "And if I could prove it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 529935.0,
      "end_time": 532888.0,
      "text": "then we would have to end up together eventually."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 533720.0,
      "end_time": 535808.0,
      "text": "This is the real madness,"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 535832.0,
      "end_time": 538227.0,
      "text": "because there is no cosmic rule"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 538251.0,
      "end_time": 541613.0,
      "text": "that says that great suffering equals great reward,"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 542148.0,
      "end_time": 546520.0,
      "text": "but we talk about love as if this is true."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 547133.0,
      "end_time": 550809.0,
      "text": "Our experiences of love are both biological and cultural."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 551444.0,
      "end_time": 553902.0,
      "text": "Our biology tells us that love is good"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 553927.0,
      "end_time": 557810.0,
      "text": "by activating these reward circuits in our brain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 557105.0,
      "end_time": 561725.0,
      "text": "and it tells us that love is painful when, after a fight or a breakup,"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 561749.0,
      "end_time": 564359.0,
      "text": "that neurochemical reward is withdrawn."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 564825.0,
      "end_time": 567267.0,
      "text": "And in fact -- and maybe you've heard this --"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 567291.0,
      "end_time": 569135.0,
      "text": "neurochemically speaking,"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 569159.0,
      "end_time": 572593.0,
      "text": "going through a breakup is a lot like going through cocaine withdrawal,"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 573345.0,
      "end_time": 574981.0,
      "text": "which I find reassuring."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 575500.0,
      "end_time": 576155.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 576736.0,
      "end_time": 579568.0,
      "text": "And then our culture uses language"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 579592.0,
      "end_time": 582372.0,
      "text": "to shape and reinforce these ideas about love."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 582397.0,
      "end_time": 585210.0,
      "text": "In this case, we're talking about metaphors about pain"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 585450.0,
      "end_time": 586560.0,
      "text": "and addiction and madness."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 587496.0,
      "end_time": 589939.0,
      "text": "It's kind of an interesting feedback loop."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 589964.0,
      "end_time": 593481.0,
      "text": "Love is powerful and at times painful,"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 593505.0,
      "end_time": 596270.0,
      "text": "and we express this in our words and stories,"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 596852.0,
      "end_time": 599350.0,
      "text": "but then our words and stories prime us"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 599374.0,
      "end_time": 602836.0,
      "text": "to expect love to be powerful and painful."
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 603625.0,
      "end_time": 606798.0,
      "text": "What's interesting to me is that all of this happens"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 606822.0,
      "end_time": 609545.0,
      "text": "in a culture that values lifelong monogamy."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 610328.0,
      "end_time": 612389.0,
      "text": "It seems like we want it both ways:"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 612413.0,
      "end_time": 614764.0,
      "text": "we want love to feel like madness,"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 615388.0,
      "end_time": 618534.0,
      "text": "and we want it to last an entire lifetime."
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 619231.0,
      "end_time": 620794.0,
      "text": "That sounds terrible."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 620818.0,
      "end_time": 622347.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 623523.0,
      "end_time": 625119.0,
      "text": "To reconcile this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 625143.0,
      "end_time": 630168.0,
      "text": "we need to either change our culture or change our expectations."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 631780.0,
      "end_time": 634670.0,
      "text": "So, imagine if we were all less passive in love."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 635312.0,
      "end_time": 639458.0,
      "text": "If we were more assertive, more open-mined, more generous"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 639482.0,
      "end_time": 642783.0,
      "text": "and instead of falling in love,"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 642807.0,
      "end_time": 645320.0,
      "text": "we stepped into love."
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 645893.0,
      "end_time": 647822.0,
      "text": "I know that this is asking a lot,"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 647846.0,
      "end_time": 651320.0,
      "text": "but I'm not actually the first person to suggest this."
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 652682.0,
      "end_time": 655191.0,
      "text": "In their book, \"Metaphors We Live By,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 655215.0,
      "end_time": 660329.0,
      "text": "linguists Mark Johnson and George Lakoff suggest a really interesting solution"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 660353.0,
      "end_time": 661570.0,
      "text": "to this dilemma,"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 662161.0,
      "end_time": 664577.0,
      "text": "which is to change our metaphors."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 665465.0,
      "end_time": 669882.0,
      "text": "They argue that metaphors really do shape the way we experience the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 670741.0,
      "end_time": 674239.0,
      "text": "and that they can even act as a guide for future actions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 674263.0,
      "end_time": 676151.0,
      "text": "like self-fulfilling prophecies."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 677159.0,
      "end_time": 680715.0,
      "text": "Johnson and Lakoff suggest a new metaphor for love:"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 681647.0,
      "end_time": 683761.0,
      "text": "love as a collaborative work of art."
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 684542.0,
      "end_time": 687592.0,
      "text": "I really like this way of thinking about love."
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 688698.0,
      "end_time": 692220.0,
      "text": "Linguists talk about metaphors as having entailments,"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 692244.0,
      "end_time": 696400.0,
      "text": "which is essentially a way of considering all the implications of,"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 696640.0,
      "end_time": 698996.0,
      "text": "or ideas contained within, a given metaphor."
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 699200.0,
      "end_time": 701929.0,
      "text": "And Johnson and Lakoff talk about everything"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 701953.0,
      "end_time": 704105.0,
      "text": "that collaborating on a work of art entails:"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 704646.0,
      "end_time": 708800.0,
      "text": "effort, compromise, patience, shared goals."
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 709325.0,
      "end_time": 713155.0,
      "text": "These ideas align nicely with our cultural investment"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 713179.0,
      "end_time": 715252.0,
      "text": "in long-term romantic commitment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 715276.0,
      "end_time": 718887.0,
      "text": "but they also work well for other kinds of relationships --"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 719690.0,
      "end_time": 725346.0,
      "text": "short-term, casual, polyamorous, non-monogamous, asexual --"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 725370.0,
      "end_time": 729255.0,
      "text": "because this metaphor brings much more complex ideas"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 729279.0,
      "end_time": 731319.0,
      "text": "to the experience of loving someone."
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 732340.0,
      "end_time": 736734.0,
      "text": "So if love is a collaborative work of art,"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 736758.0,
      "end_time": 740170.0,
      "text": "then love is an aesthetic experience."
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 741194.0,
      "end_time": 743890.0,
      "text": "Love is unpredictable,"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 743823.0,
      "end_time": 745847.0,
      "text": "love is creative,"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 746568.0,
      "end_time": 750701.0,
      "text": "love requires communication and discipline,"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 750725.0,
      "end_time": 753914.0,
      "text": "it is frustrating and emotionally demanding."
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 754347.0,
      "end_time": 757697.0,
      "text": "And love involves both joy and pain."
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 758412.0,
      "end_time": 762310.0,
      "text": "Ultimately, each experience of love is different."
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 763429.0,
      "end_time": 765550.0,
      "text": "When I was younger,"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 765800.0,
      "end_time": 769748.0,
      "text": "it never occurred to me that I was allowed to demand more from love,"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 769772.0,
      "end_time": 773465.0,
      "text": "that I didn't have to just accept whatever love offered."
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 774445.0,
      "end_time": 777774.0,
      "text": "When 14-year-old Juliet first meets --"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 777798.0,
      "end_time": 781723.0,
      "text": "or, when 14-year-old Juliet cannot be with Romeo,"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 781747.0,
      "end_time": 784889.0,
      "text": "whom she has met four days ago ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 785836.0,
      "end_time": 789646.0,
      "text": "she does not feel disappointed or angsty."
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 790192.0,
      "end_time": 791549.0,
      "text": "Where is she?"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 791573.0,
      "end_time": 792867.0,
      "text": "She wants to die."
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 793406.0,
      "end_time": 794556.0,
      "text": "Right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 794581.0,
      "end_time": 797500.0,
      "text": "And just as a refresher, at this point in the play,"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 797740.0,
      "end_time": 798382.0,
      "text": "act three of five,"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 798406.0,
      "end_time": 800227.0,
      "text": "Romeo is not dead."
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 800811.0,
      "end_time": 802151.0,
      "text": "He's alive,"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 802175.0,
      "end_time": 803563.0,
      "text": "he's healthy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 803587.0,
      "end_time": 805781.0,
      "text": "he's just been banished from the city."
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 806625.0,
      "end_time": 813240.0,
      "text": "I understand that 16th-century Verona is unlike contemporary North America,"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 813480.0,
      "end_time": 816260.0,
      "text": "and yet when I first read this play,"
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 816500.0,
      "end_time": 818443.0,
      "text": "also at age 14,"
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 818467.0,
      "end_time": 821150.0,
      "text": "Juliet's suffering made sense to me."
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 822465.0,
      "end_time": 827822.0,
      "text": "Reframing love as something I get to create with someone I admire,"
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 827846.0,
      "end_time": 830290.0,
      "text": "rather than something that just happens to me"
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 830314.0,
      "end_time": 832836.0,
      "text": "without my control or consent,"
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 832860.0,
      "end_time": 834465.0,
      "text": "is empowering."
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 834949.0,
      "end_time": 836567.0,
      "text": "It's still hard."
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 836591.0,
      "end_time": 842123.0,
      "text": "Love still feels totally maddening and crushing some days,"
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 842147.0,
      "end_time": 844262.0,
      "text": "and when I feel really frustrated,"
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 844286.0,
      "end_time": 845616.0,
      "text": "I have to remind myself:"
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 846165.0,
      "end_time": 849509.0,
      "text": "my job in this relationship is to talk to my partner"
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 849533.0,
      "end_time": 851584.0,
      "text": "about what I want to make together."
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 852561.0,
      "end_time": 855355.0,
      "text": "This isn't easy, either."
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 855926.0,
      "end_time": 859695.0,
      "text": "But it's just so much better than the alternative,"
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 859842.0,
      "end_time": 862619.0,
      "text": "which is that thing that feels like madness."
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 863747.0,
      "end_time": 869325.0,
      "text": "This version of love is not about winning or losing someone's affection."
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 869931.0,
      "end_time": 873529.0,
      "text": "Instead, it requires that you trust your partner"
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 873553.0,
      "end_time": 876627.0,
      "text": "and talk about things when trusting feels difficult,"
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 876651.0,
      "end_time": 879970.0,
      "text": "which sounds so simple,"
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 879121.0,
      "end_time": 883617.0,
      "text": "but is actually a kind of revolutionary, radical act."
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 884232.0,
      "end_time": 888236.0,
      "text": "And this is because you get to stop thinking about yourself"
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 888400.0,
      "end_time": 891540.0,
      "text": "and what you're gaining or losing in your relationship,"
    },
    {
      "index": 289,
      "start_time": 891565.0,
      "end_time": 894962.0,
      "text": "and you get to start thinking about what you have to offer."
    },
    {
      "index": 290,
      "start_time": 895981.0,
      "end_time": 899386.0,
      "text": "This version of love allows us to say things like,"
    },
    {
      "index": 291,
      "start_time": 899410.0,
      "end_time": 904240.0,
      "text": "\"Hey, we're not very good collaborators. Maybe this isn't for us.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 292,
      "start_time": 904862.0,
      "end_time": 908723.0,
      "text": "Or, \"That relationship was shorter than I had planned,"
    },
    {
      "index": 293,
      "start_time": 908748.0,
      "end_time": 910920.0,
      "text": "but it was still kind of beautiful.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 294,
      "start_time": 912600.0,
      "end_time": 914795.0,
      "text": "The beautiful thing about the collaborative work of art"
    },
    {
      "index": 295,
      "start_time": 914820.0,
      "end_time": 917711.0,
      "text": "is that it will not paint or draw or sculpt itself."
    },
    {
      "index": 296,
      "start_time": 918268.0,
      "end_time": 921847.0,
      "text": "This version of love allows us to decide what it looks like."
    },
    {
      "index": 297,
      "start_time": 922203.0,
      "end_time": 923353.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 298,
      "start_time": 923378.0,
      "end_time": 927910.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}